# Leash — Data Model

## Entities

### Entity: Harness

The core Rust runtime library. Reads hardware config, manages safety gates, routes commands to adapters.

```yaml
entity: Harness
type: entity
properties:
  name:
    type: string
    required: true
  adapters:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Feature-gated adapter list
  safety_gates:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Active safety gate stack
states: [planned, mapped, extracted, stabilized, released]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → extracted → stabilized → released
```

### Entity: CLI

Command-line interface and localhost HTTP compatibility server. Thin shell around the harness.

```yaml
entity: CLI
type: entity
properties:
  http_port:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 9000
  commands:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Subcommands (serve, status, estop)
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: MCPServer

MCP stdio server exposing robot tools to local LLM clients. Tool set: motor, sensor, estop, status.

```yaml
entity: MCPServer
type: entity
properties:
  tools:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Exposed MCP tool list
  transport:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [stdio]
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: UGVAdapter

Feature-gated Waveshare Ubuntu UGV hardware adapter. Only compiles when `--features ugv` is set.

```yaml
entity: UGVAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "Waveshare Ubuntu UGV"
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "ugv"
  motor_channels:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 4
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated, documented]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated → documented
```

### Entity: Bridge

Compatibility layer for existing robot bridge clients. Maps legacy APIs to the harness runtime.

```yaml
entity: Bridge
type: entity
properties:
  clients:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Supported bridge client list
  shim_layer:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Compatibility shim path
states: [planned, mapped, documented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → documented → tested
```

### Entity: Safety

Smoke-test scripts for MCP, HTTP, and safety gate verification. Gates every release.

```yaml
entity: Safety
type: entity
properties:
  test_targets:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: MCP, HTTP, safety-gates
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "smoke"
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

### Entity: ReleasePipeline

Packages the harness for crates.io and GitHub binary releases.

```yaml
entity: ReleasePipeline
type: entity
properties:
  targets:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: crates.io, GitHub binaries
  platforms:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: linux-x86_64, macos-arm64
states: [planned, configured, publishing]
lifecycle: planned → configured → publishing
```

### Entity: Bootstrap

Crate skeleton, license (MIT+trademark), CI pipeline, repo provenance.

```yaml
entity: Bootstrap
type: entity
properties:
  license:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "MIT+trademark"
  ci_platform:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "GitHub Actions"
  crate_name:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "leash"
states: [planned, bootstrapped, ci_green]
lifecycle: planned → bootstrapped → ci_green
```

## Relationships

### Relationship: Bootstrap → Harness

```yaml
relationship: Bootstrap → Harness
verb: provisions
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
```

### Relationship: Harness → CLI

```yaml
relationship: Harness → CLI
verb: powers
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
```

### Relationship: Harness → MCPServer

```yaml
relationship: Harness → MCPServer
verb: powers
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
```

### Relationship: Harness → Bridge

```yaml
relationship: Harness → Bridge
verb: exposes_through
cardinality: 1:many
required: true
```

### Relationship: UGVAdapter → Harness

```yaml
relationship: UGVAdapter → Harness
verb: adapts
cardinality: 1:1
required: false
description: Only when --features ugv is enabled
```

### Relationship: Safety → Harness

```yaml
relationship: Safety → Harness
verb: gates
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
```

### Relationship: Safety → UGVAdapter

```yaml
relationship: Safety → UGVAdapter
verb: gates
cardinality: 1:1
required: false
```

### Relationship: ReleasePipeline → Harness

```yaml
relationship: ReleasePipeline → Harness
verb: packages
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
```

### Relationship: Bridge → CLI

```yaml
relationship: Bridge → CLI
verb: documents_for
cardinality: many:1
required: true
```
